cal communities in order to sustain and enlarge its political and economic footprint. Promoting good corporate governance, as well as social and environmental responsibility, would help.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Aug 2021) 0aCambodia—Foreign relations. 0aCambodia—Politics and government. 0aCambodia—Relations—China. 0aChina—Relations—Cambodia. 0aInvestments, ChinesezCambodia. 0aInvestments, Chinese—Cambodia. 0aInvestments, Chinese—Southeast Asia. 0aInvestments, ForeignzCambodia. 0aPolitical Economy. 4aPolitical Economy. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / Political Economy.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus eBook-Package 2017z978311071954308iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertISEAS Complete eBook-Package 2017z978311066298608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertISEAS eBook Package 2015-2017z978311060667640uhttps://doi.org/10.1355/978981478680540uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9789814786805423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9789814786805.jpg  a978-3-11-060667-6  ISEAS eBook Package 2015-2017c2015d2017  a978-3-11-066298-6  ISEAS Complete eBook-Package 2017b2017  a978-3-11-071954-3  DG Plus eBook-Package 2017b2017  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_SN  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_SN  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aEBA_STMALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA12STME  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK